column5: I had hopes of going out again and beating up on some fishies seeing as I was having so much fun yesterday. When I got home there were 1,  then 2, bushels of tomatoes, a 1/4 bushel of peppers, and a 1/2 bushel of pears waiting on the doorstep. So much for any fishing plans.  Round one produced the following. 4 pans of pear cobbler  1 1/2 gallons of salsa  Plus I managed to bag and freeze another 60lbs of tomato. I am now on round two. In the pots are 4 gallons of pasta sauce and another gallon of my "Roadkill Chilli"  Once I get that done I still have this to process.   It can be a long cold winter, but we won't starve   I'll surely need to go fishinh tomorrow after this is all done.
Well congratulations, at least someone knows how to put good food to use.  Nothing as good as the home made stuff.  Never tried pear cobbler, but made some pear pies.
Lucky guy! All we ever get dropped on our doorstep are 50 pound zucchini. Try and make a cobbler out of that!
Can you tell me why the red panties and black strap bra are doing on the floor?  cheers Streamerguy
Im thinking pickled roasted red peppers? Yummy.
Wow, all I got was 1 green pepper and a handful of small tomatoes, which are still green and I'm worried about frost now.  You did well  Joey
Care to trade for a monster zucchini Joey?
all I saw were the candy apples-mmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmm !!!!!!!

If I gotta do all the cooking, wifey's got to do the entertaining  Wild Posted Today, 06:32 PM Lucky guy! All we ever get dropped on our doorstep are 50 pound zucchini. Try and make a cobbler out of that   Battered deep fried zucchini sticks with Tzatziki or wild garlic and chive dip. Yum Yum The joys of living in a farm community. A lot of barter.
You know Bruce I think Tzatziki will work perfect great suggestion!
well when's dinner??...perhaps a fish fry is in order soon while it is still nice out..I got some in the freezer
Next thing I know you'll have 1/2 of OFC at my door plate in hand   I may have to find me another fryer or 2
